        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 1:34PM EDT by NWS Albany NY</headline>
        <description>At 134 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Olivebridge, or 11 miles northwest of New Paltz, moving northeast at
20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Ashokan, Rolling Meadows, Samsonville, Maple Hill, Glenford,
Palentown, Atwood, Pacama, Brodhead, Liebhardt, Hickorybush,
Hillside, Stone Ridge, Marbletown, Montoma, Creeklocks, Morgan Hill,
Hurley, Saint Remy, and Mettacahonts.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM EDT for
east central New York.</instruction>
